---
const pillars = [
  {
    title: 'Sovereign by design',
    body: 'Run it where you need it. Our cloud, your VPC, your laptop, your air-gapped Kubernetes cluster. The architecture is built for the self-hosted case — which means the cloud case inherits real isolation, not retrofitted it.',
    symbol: '◉',
  },
  {
    title: 'Model-agnostic',
    body: 'Local models via Ollama, API providers like OpenAI and Anthropic, or your own inference endpoint. Mix and match per pipeline step. Change a line of YAML, not a line of code.',
    symbol: '◈',
  },
  {
    title: 'Open source core',
    body: 'Apache 2.0 licensed. The cloud runs the same code you can read, fork, and self-host. No proprietary extraction logic, no closed model pipeline, no "here\'s the community edition and here\'s the real one."',
    symbol: '◇',
  },
];
---

<section class="sovereign">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="label-row">
      <p class="section-label">
        <span class="num">05</span>
        <span>Data sovereignty</span>
      </p>
      <hr class="rule flex-1" />
    </div>

    <div class="sovereign-head">
      <h2 class="display">
        Your data is yours.<br/>
        Always.
      </h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Most document processing platforms were designed around a single assumption: that you'll upload your data to their cloud and trust them with it. Koji starts from the opposite premise — and the cloud inherits that assumption, too.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pillars">
      {pillars.map((p, i) => (
        <article class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-num-row">
            <span class="pillar-symbol">{p.symbol}</span>
            <span class="pillar-num">0{i + 1}</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="display pillar-title">{p.title}</h3>
          <p class="pillar-body">{p.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sovereign {
    padding: var(--section-pad) 0;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--cream);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .sovereign > * { position: relative; z-index: 1; }

  .sovereign .section-label { color: var(--cream-4); }
  .sovereign .section-label .num { color: var(--vermillion); }
  .sovereign .rule { border-top-color: rgba(244, 238, 226, 0.18); }

  .label-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 4.5rem;
  }

  .flex-1 { flex: 1; }

  .sovereign-head {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.7fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: end;
    margin-bottom: 6rem;
  }

  .sovereign-head h2 {
    color: var(--cream);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .sovereign-head .lede {
    color: var(--cream-3);
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Pillars ============================================================= */

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2px;
    background: rgba(244, 238, 226, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(244, 238, 226, 0.1);
  }

  .pillar {
    background: var(--ink);
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: background 0.4s;
  }

  .pillar:hover {
    background: rgba(244, 238, 226, 0.03);
  }

  .pillar-num-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(244, 238, 226, 0.12);
  }

  .pillar-symbol {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--vermillion);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .pillar-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--cream-4);
  }

  .pillar-title {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--cream);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72, 'SOFT' 50;
  }

  .pillar-body {
    color: var(--cream-3);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    max-width: 36ch;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .sovereign-head {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .pillars {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
